an enodeB including a first RF transceiver located at a first remote location for transmitting RF signals over RF communications links;
consumer premises equipment including a second RF transceiver located at a second remote location for transmitting the RF signals over the RF communications links;
at least one repeater for communicating with a plurality of remote locations over the RF communications links, wherein the at least one repeater further comprises:
multiple input multiple output (MIMO) transmission circuitry for transmitting signals and receiving signals over the RF communications links to the plurality of remote locations, wherein the MIMO transmission circuitry limits interference between the transmitted signals and the received signals;
full-duplex transmission circuitry for processing the transmitted signals and the received signals over the RF communications links using full-duplex communications with the plurality of remote locations; and
wherein the at least one repeater relays the RF signals between the first RF transceiver at the enodeB at the first remote location and the second RF transceiver at the consumer premises equipment at the second remote location.

